{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0ee02e4a-29ee-4108-bd2c-8804bfa44ece","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped (not failed) in test results and display your reason message.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a1d3ff0-7c26-46db-b724-aadd4842b4b5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":191,"requestId":"9827:180764:1AB6D0:22FAAB:69FFDC0D"},"id":"0ed9ccff-693f-4e63-8e10-b28bca4f78fb","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:14:58.910Z","parentId":"ec18874c-da39-4dd5-b96c-4eed42de360a"}
